Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Initial app scaffold: Next.js UI, API routes, Prisma
 schema, demo data, and Docker

### Motivation
- Provide a runnable demo scaffold for the Aria migration operations product to accelerate development and reviews.
- Offer a review-required AI-assisted workflow surface with source-linked field review, update ingestion, and document pipeline abstractions.
- Include infrastructure and developer DX files so contributors can run the app locally and seed a demo dataset.

### Description
- Added a full Next.js App Router application with landing, auth, and authenticated workspace pages and UI primitives in `components/` and `app/` to render an operations dashboard and matter workflows.
- Implemented lightweight service adapters and demo implementations for AI (`lib/services/ai-adapter.ts`), document pipeline (`lib/services/document-pipeline.ts`), and update ingestion/connectors (`lib/connectors/update-connector.ts`, `lib/services/update-ingestion.ts`), plus API routes under `app/api/*` to exercise them.
- Added domain types, seeded demo data, demo repository helpers (`lib/domain.ts`, `lib/demo-data.ts`, `lib/data/demo-repository.ts`), and a full Prisma schema, SQL migration, and seed script under `prisma/` to model workspace, matters, documents, updates, tasks, AI chat threads and audit events.
- Included developer tooling and runtime configuration: `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `.env.example`, `README.md`, `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `next.config.mjs`, Tailwind/PostCSS configs, `eslint` config, and utility helpers like `lib/utils.ts`.

### Testing
- No automated tests were executed as part of this change; the PR provides startup and seed scripts (`npm run dev`, `npm run build`, `npm run prisma:generate`, `npm run prisma:migrate`, `npm run prisma:seed`) for local verification of the app and database seed process.
